Camtek Advances Most in 2 Months on $4 Million Asian Order

-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-03-06T14:45:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-06/camtek-advances-most-in-14-months-on-4-million-asian-order.html
Camtek Ltd. gained the most in
almost two months after the maker of optical-inspection systems
received a $4 million repeat order from an unidentified Asian
supplier.  The shares rose 8.6 percent, the biggest increase since
Jan. 12, to 15.36 shekels at the 4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv ,
giving the Migdal Haemek, Israel-based company a market value of
438 million shekels ($121 million).  The order is for systems that are expected to be installed
during the second quarter, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ronit Goodman in Tel Aviv at 
 rgoodman9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  